# Python FastAPI Cursor Rules

## Stack
- Python 3.11+ with FastAPI
- Pydantic v2 for validation
- SQLAlchemy 2.0 + Alembic
- pytest + httpx for testing
- uv for package management

## Code Style
- Type hints required on all functions
- Pydantic models for request/response schemas
- Dependency injection via FastAPI `Depends()`
- Async endpoints by default (`async def`)

## Project Structure
- `app/routers/` — route definitions
- `app/services/` — business logic
- `app/models/` — SQLAlchemy models
- `app/schemas/` — Pydantic schemas
- `app/dependencies/` — FastAPI dependencies

## Response Schemas
- Separate Request / Response schemas (never expose DB models directly)
- Use `response_model=` on every endpoint
- Include pagination for list endpoints

## Error Handling
- Raise `HTTPException` with meaningful status codes
- Custom exception handlers for domain errors
- Never return 500 with internal details in production

## Testing
- Use `TestClient` or `AsyncClient` from httpx
- Test each endpoint: success, validation error, auth error
- Use fixtures for DB setup/teardown
